05/02/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- After returning from a visit to Kosovo on Monday (February 4th), Albanian Foreign Minister Lulzim Basha said the Kosovo Albanian leadership has completed all preparations related to declaring independence from Serbia. Basha, who met with Kosovo President Fatmir Sejdiu, Prime Minister Hashim Thaci and Parliament Speaker Jakup Krasniqi, said independence would be announced in full co-ordination with Washington and Brussels. He declined to give a specific date.
In Pristina, Krasniqi said it will be sometime this month. He also praised the re-election of Serbian President Boris Tadic. (RFE, Balkanweb, Kosovalive - 04/02/08) 
